annotation protocol for ted-mdb.1976.xlsx 
------------------------------------------

Insecurities and Issues

- prioritization of REF_AUTO for compounds with proper nouns, even though they are not the syntactic head. Examples: "NASA" Laboratory (51, 132), "Hubble" Telescope (213), Oort Cloud (341).

	- TODO: git issue
	- general guideline: if syntactically transparent, annotate the head, if not, annotate the first word
	- This includes compounds (with hypen) in German. Linguistically, the morphological head is the last element.
	- At the moment, decided by parser. We need our own tokenizer. First part of a compound should not be a separate token. See github issues.

- handling "wir"
	- if replaceable with "man": REF=GEN
		- ok, add to guidelines
	- otherwise if used for entire humanity: ID "menschen"
		- ok, but don't call that "generic"
	- ID "wir" for a hypothetical subject in a thought experiment, representing loosely a group of speaker and listener (210-479)
		- may be distinguished from generic/all humanity "wir", but not from other groupings of speaker and listener in reality or other thought experiments. Group identity by (complete) member identity.
	- ID "team" for a group comprising the speaker and colleagues, used in the context of explaining a solution to the problem of non-visibility (833-1165)
		- exclusive we, ok
		

